ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='I see several issues already:\n\n1. In `adapter.go`, there are many i
nstances of `data, _ := proto.Marshal(payload)` - errors are ignored. This is a 
code quality issue.\n2. In `bus.go`, the `Publish` method launches goroutines wi
thout any recovery mechanism (`go func(handler Handler) { ... }`). If a handler 
panics, it will crash the program. No panic recovery.\n3. In `consumer.go`, `ret
ryOrDLQ` ACKs the message before checking retry count and potentially requeueing
it. This means if the requeue fails, the message is lost. Also `strconv.Atoi` er
ror is ignored.\n4. In `publisher.go`, `streamKey` uses `int(userID) % p.partiti
on` - on 32-bit systems this could overflow for large userIDs. Better to use `in
t64` arithmetic or `math.Abs`.\n5. In `idempotent.go`, `IsProcessed` returns `va
l == "1"` - if the value is anything else, it returns false instead of an error.
This is okay but could be stricter.\n\nLet me continue reading the other changed
files to get a full picture.',
    encrypted=None
)
