ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Let me now look at the test files for eventbus to see if there are an
y issues I should note, and check the wire_gen.go files to verify DI is correct.
I also need to check gofmt status and look for any other architectural issues.\n
\nKey issues I\'ve found so far:\n1. **adapter.go**: Multiple instances of `data
, _ := proto.Marshal(payload)` - errors are silently ignored. This is bad practi
ce.\n2. **bus.go**: `Publish` method spawns goroutines without panic recovery. I
f a handler panics, the whole process crashes.\n3. **publisher.go**: `streamKey`
uses `int(userID) % p.partition` which can overflow on 32-bit systems for large 
userIDs.\n4. **consumer.go**: In `retryOrDLQ`, `strconv.Atoi` error is ignored. 
Also, the message is ACKed before being potentially requeued or sent to DLQ, whi
ch means if requeue/DLQ fails, the message is lost.\n5. **consumer.go**: `ensure
ConsumerGroup` uses string comparison for error checking (`err.Error() != "BUSYG
ROUP Consumer Group name already exists"`), which is fragile.\n6. **Test coverag
e**: The new `eventbus` package has good coverage (83.9%), but the biz layers th
at were modified (`wapi`, `wcity/wcc`, `wmix`) have 0% test coverage for the new
event publishing logic.\n7. **Architecture**: Biz layer depends on `eventbus.Str
eamPublisher` and `eventbus.EventAdapter` - this is acceptable as eventbus is in
`internal/pkg` which is a shared package, not data layer directly. The injection
goes through data layer providers. This seems okay.\n\nWait, looking at the arch
itecture more carefully:\n- `internal/biz/wapi/market.go` depends on `eventbus.S
treamPublisher` and creates `eventbus.EventAdapter` directly\n- `internal/biz/wc
ity/wcc/building_map.go` does the same\n- `internal/biz/wmix/mixing.go` does the
same\n\nIn Kratos architecture, typically:\n- Biz layer should not directly depe
nd on infrastructure\n- Data layer provides the interfaces\n- But `eventbus` is 
in `internal/pkg/eventbus` which might be considered a shared package\n\nActuall
y, looking at the code, `eventbus.StreamPublisher` is an interface defined in `i
nternal/pkg/eventbus`. In clean architecture, Biz should define its own interfac
es and Data should implement them. However, the project already has patterns whe
re biz directly imports from `internal/pkg` packages.\n\nLet me check how the ex
isting repo pattern works to understand if this is a deviation.',
    encrypted=None
)
